Name: showsRetryUntilPollingThenGetsUsers(Quest)
Description: Feature demo: retryUntil â€” poll a custom condition every 1s (max 10s) and, once satisfied, proceed with a normal GET and assert 200.

Name: showsLateCraftModelMaterializedOnDemand(Quest, Late)
Description: Combines a GET and POST where the POST body is built lazily via Late<@Craft> (materialized only when create() is called).

Name: showsSwitchingRingsForLoginThenApiCall(Quest, LoginDto)
Description: Demonstrates switching rings (services): use a custom ring to log in + header wiring, then return to RING_OF_API for the GET.

Name: showsAuthenticateViaApiWithJourneySetupAndRipperCleanup(Quest)
Description: Executes a full user lifecycle using AuthenticateViaApi for auth, Journey preconditions for setup, and Ripper for cleanup.

Name: showsChainedRequestsAndUsingStorage(Quest)
Description: Chains requests: read an id from the stored list response and reuse it as a path param in the next call.

Name: showsMixOfCraftAndLateCraftInChainedFlow(Quest, CreateUserDto, Late)
Description: Mixes eager @Craft and lazy Late<@Craft>: eager model is ready up-front; the Late model is instantiated via create() at use time.

Name: showsNegativeLoginMissingPasswordWithErrorAssertion(Quest)
Description: Shows negative testing with requestAndValidate: build a DTO missing password, call POST /login, assert 400 and error via JSON path.

Name: showsManualLifecycleWithExplicitLoginAndTokenHandling(Quest)
Description: Executes the user lifecycle manually using explicit login, token handling, create, validate, and delete.

Name: showsJourneySetupWithRipperCleanup(Quest)
Description: Executes the user lifecycle with @Journey data setup and @Ripper cleanup after the test.

Name: showsPreconditionsWithJourneyDataSetup(Quest)
Description: Executes the user lifecycle using @Journey to prepare users before the test body runs.

Name: showsEncapsulatedValidationUsingEvolutionRing(Quest)
Description: Executes the user lifecycle using a custom evolution ring that encapsulates validation logic.

Name: showsSoftAssertionsAfterFindingUserByFirstNameFromStorage(Quest)
Description: Reads the list from storage, finds a user by first name, and validates the full user with soft assertions.

Name: showsSlimmerTestsViaCustomServiceRing(Quest, LoginDto)
Description: Shows how a custom service ring can slim down tests by encapsulating the full validation flow.

Name: showsLoginWithDtoAndTokenAssertion(Quest)
Description: Shows login POST with DTO credentials and asserting a non-null token via JSON path.

Name: showsGetWithPathParamAndJsonPathValidation(Quest)
Description: Shows GET with a path parameter using requestAndValidate and validating a field via JSON path.

Name: showsApiLevelAuthenticationWithAuthenticateViaApi(Quest)
Description: Executes the user lifecycle using @AuthenticateViaApi instead of manual token handling.

Name: showsCraftModelAsRequestWithSoftAssertion(Quest, CreateUserDto)
Description: Creates a user from an eager @Craft model and validates with a soft assertion.

Name: showsTokenReuseFromStorageAcrossRequests(Quest, LoginDto)
Description: Logs in using @Craft credentials, stores the token, and reuses it as a header in the next GET call.

Name: showsPostWithDtoAndSimpleBodyAssertions(Quest)
Description: Shows POST with a DTO request body using requestAndValidate and simple body assertions.

Name: showsBasicGetWithQueryParamAndMinimalAssertions(Quest)
Description: Shows GET with a query parameter via quest.use(RING_OF_API) + requestAndValidate; minimal status/header checks.

Name: showsComprehensiveAssertionsOnUsersList(Quest)
Description: Showcases many assertion types in one GET: status/headers, numeric comparisons, regex, contains(all/any), length, null checks...

Name: showsRequestThenValidateWithPlainJUnitAssertions(Quest)
Description: Uses request() + validate(): make a request, retrieve the stored response, and assert with plain JUnit (no DSL).
